## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests, 0 real verifications.** This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test suite — every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called so coverage tools report ~95%, but almost nothing is actually asserted. Bugs will sail through these tests undetected.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 |
| 🟠 High | 1 |
| 🟡 Medium | 2 |
| Total | **9** |

---

### 🔴 Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic — entire test class)

The suite methodically calls every public method on `ProductCatalog` in declaration order with **zero or trivial** assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **no assertion at all**; the other 4 use only `Assert.IsNotNull`, which merely checks that a reference was returned — not that the *correct value* was returned.

**Tests with zero assertions:**

| Test | Line | What's unverified |
|------|------|-------------------|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17 | Product was actually stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33 | Price actually changed to 14.99 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39 | Product was actually deleted |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 63 | Count value (not even captured!) |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69 | Prices were reduced by 10% |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85 | Parsed data was saved correctly |

**Tests with only `Assert.IsNotNull` (insufficient):**

| Test | Line | What's unverified |
|------|------|-------------------|
| `GetProduct_Works` | 25 | SKU, Name, Price of returned product |
| `SearchProducts_Works` | 46 | Result count, whether correct product matched |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` | 55 | Collection count, contents |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` | 77 | CSV format, field values |

**Concrete fixes — before/after:**

```csharp
// ❌ BEFORE: AddProduct_Works (line 17) — no assertion
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// ✅ AFTER: verify the product is retrievable with correct values
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

